Lots of work has been done to transform the City Hall into the Parliamentary precinct. CAPE TOWN - The stage is set - literally - for South Africa's first major political event of the year. Cape Town City Hall has been transformed into the Parliamentary precinct for this year's State of the Nation Address. READ: Presiding officers say it's all systems go It's the first time Sona will be held outside Parliament, due to a fire that gutted the National Assembly last month. eNCA's Monique Mortlock shares more details in the video above.